  <title>
    <phrase>Sobel</phrase>
  </title>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Filters</primary>
    <secondary>Edge Detect</secondary>
    <tertiary>Sobel</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Sobel</primary>
  </indexterm>
  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Overview</phrase>
    </title>
    <figure>
      <title>
        <phrase>Applying example of the Sobel filter</phrase>
      </title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/filters/examples/taj_orig.jpg" format="JPG"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>
          <para>Original image</para>
        </caption>
      </mediaobject>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/filters/examples/edge-taj-sobel.jpg" format="JPG"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>
          <para>Filter <quote>Sobel</quote> applied</para>
        </caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>
      Sobel's filter detects horizontal and vertical edges separately on a
      scaled image. Color images are turned into RGB scaled images. As with
      the Laplace filter, the result is a transparent image with black lines
      and some rest of colors.
    </para>
  </sect3>
  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Activate the filter</phrase>
    </title>
    <para>
      You can find this filter through
      <menuchoice><guimenu>Filters</guimenu><guisubmenu>Edge detect</guisubmenu><guimenuitem><accel>S</accel>obel</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.
    </para>
  </sect3>
  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Options</phrase>
    </title>
    <figure>
      <title>
        <phrase>
          Sobel filter options
        </phrase>
      </title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/filters/sobel-options.png" format="PNG"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Parameters Settings</term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para><guilabel>Sobel Horizontally</guilabel>: Renders near
                horizontal edges.
              </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para><guilabel>Sobel Vertically</guilabel>: Renders near
                vertical edges.
              </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para><guilabel>Keep sign of result</guilabel>: This option works
                when one and only one direction is selected: it gives a
                flat relief with bumps and hollows to the image.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Keep sign of result</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            This option allows you to set how the filter will work if you
            have selected one direction for use only: an embossed grayscale
            image will be created.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
